16/07/2007
ZAGREB, Croatia -- The Zagreb County Court begins hearings in the so-called Maestro case, stemming from the corruption scandal at the Croatian Privatisation Fund (HFP), on Tuesday (July 17th). 
Investigative Judge Boris Ivancic said on Sunday that charges have been filed against eight people, including three HFP vice chairmen, for abuse of power, corruption and misappropriation of over 1m euros. 
Seven people are in custody. 
(Poslovni dnevnik, Vecernji list - 16/07/07; HRT - 15/07/07)
